          <title>History of Present Illness</title>
          <text>Mr. Park is a 60-year-old male with a 4-year history of progressive right knee pain consistent with osteoarthritis. He reports pain rated 7/10 at rest and 9/10 with ambulation. He has failed conservative management including NSAIDs, physical therapy (12 sessions), and two intra-articular corticosteroid injections (last injection October 2025). Weight-bearing X-rays confirm severe tricompartmental osteoarthritis with bone-on-bone changes medially. The patient desires surgical correction and understands the risks, benefits, and alternatives including continued conservative management. He has been cleared by his cardiologist and primary care physician for elective surgery. He presents today for pre-operative history and physical prior to scheduled total right knee arthroplasty.</text>
